#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:1
msgid "How much carbon dioxide do we emit when heating our homes? This depends on three main factors:"
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:3
msgid ""
"Heated area: how large is our home and how much of it do we heat? Do we live alone in a large house or do we share a "
"small apartment? Do we heat the entire house throughout the cold season or only the rooms we use while we use them?"
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:5
msgid ""
"Energy efficiency: how much energy do we need to heat one square meter? This depends on how well insulated buildings "
"are, but also on how we ventilate our homes during winter."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:7
msgid ""
"Energy source: how do we heat? Do we use a gas boiler, an oil furnace, a fireplace, or a heat pump? The source (or "
"\"carrier\") of energy determines how much CO₂ is emitted (and where) for each kWh of heating energy we use."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:9
msgid ""
"The 2022 German national census provides spatial information that allows us to estimate each of these key variables in "
"any 100-m grid cell across Germany."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:11
msgid ""
"multiply population by the average living space per capita to obtain total living space (i.e., the space that is "
"presumably heated)."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:13
msgid ""
"calculate the average area-specific heating energy consumption (kWh per m²) of residential buildings based on "
"buildings' year of construction."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:15
msgid ""
"calculate average carbon dioxide emissions per unit of heating energy (kg per kWh) based on the proportion of buildings "
"with different heating energy carriers (e.g., gas, oil, wood, district heating, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: resources/locales/en/methodology.md:17
msgid ""
"Emission estimates are the product of total living space, average area-specific energy consumption, and average "
"emission factor."
msgstr ""

